This paper deals with the problem of domain adaptation, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision. The paper proposes a novel method for partial domain adaptation, which involves aligning the feature distributions of two domains when the classes in the two domains are not identical. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and multimedia (cs.MM). However, given that the paper focuses on image classification tasks, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.MM.
